# ─── Required for AI features ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Plate scan (/api/ai/nutrition), chat (/api/ai/chat), and the label-OCR
# fallback (/api/ai/nutrition-label) all call Gemini with this key.
GOOGLE_GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Optional — override default Gemini model. Falls back to gemini-2.5-flash.
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# ─── Optional — nutrient waterfall sources (free tiers) ─────────────────
# USDA FoodData Central — used as tier 3 in the Gemini plate-scan waterfall
# (China/Japan local DB → CalorieNinjas → USDA → Gemini estimate). Free key:
#   https://fdc.nal.usda.gov/api-key-signup.html
USDA_API_KEY=

# CalorieNinjas — used as tier 2 in the plate-scan waterfall. Free 10k/mo:
#   https://calorieninjas.com/api
CALORIE_NINJAS_API_KEY=

# ─── Optional — barcode cascade sources (free) ──────────────────────────
# Rakuten Ichiba Item Search — used for Japanese JAN barcodes when
# OpenFoodFacts and UPCitemDB miss. Cascade skips this tier silently when
# the var isn't set. Free Rakuten developer account:
#   https://webservice.rakuten.co.jp/
RAKUTEN_APPLICATION_ID=

# ─── Stripe (only needed for paywall/subscription flows) ────────────────
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# ─── Supabase auth (required for Google sign-in + trial gate) ───────────
# The login gate in middleware.ts + src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts uses these
# two vars. Missing them is allowed — the gate degrades gracefully and the
# app stays reachable locally without auth, so you can develop offline.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Create a Supabase project: https://supabase.com/dashboard
#   2. Project Settings → API → copy the Project URL and anon/public key.
#   3. Enable Google as an OAuth provider: Authentication → Providers →
#      Google. Follow the instructions to set up a Google Cloud OAuth
#      client. In the Google Cloud Console, add these Authorized Redirect
#      URIs to the OAuth client:
#         https://<your-project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#         http://localhost:3000/auth/callback   (for local dev)
#         https://<your-prod-domain>/auth/callback
#   4. Back in Supabase, paste the Google client ID + secret into the
#      Google provider settings.
#
# The site redirects unauth'd users hitting /app/* or /onboarding to /login,
# which starts the PKCE flow; /auth/callback exchanges the code for a
# session cookie. Everything else is handled by @supabase/ssr.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
